To represent `x-ms-client-flatten: true` for a top-level resource property in TypeSpec, you should use the `@flattenProperty` decorator from the `Azure.ClientGenerator.Core.Legacy` namespace. This decorator is designed to preserve the flattening behavior in the generated OpenAPI and SDKs, matching the original Swagger intent.

Here is how you can apply it in TypeSpec:

```typespec
import Azure.ClientGenerator.Core.Legacy;

/**
 * ArcSetting details.
 */
@parentResource(Cluster)
model ArcSetting is Azure.ResourceManager.ProxyResource {
  ...ResourceNameParameter;

  /** ArcSetting properties. */
  @Azure.ClientGenerator.Core.Legacy.flattenProperty
  properties: ArcSettingProperties;
