- The operation name (`listBySubscription`) can stay the same if you use @removed/@added to version the signature. The TypeSpec compiler will emit the correct operation for each version.
- If you want to keep both operations for some reason, you can use different names (e.g., `listBySubscriptionV2`), but the standard pattern is to keep the name and version the signature.
